[Adapter]
	- aims to convert one interface into another.

	* Kotlin's extension functions provide a concise and elegant way to create adapters without the need for additional classes.

	(Adapters in the real world)
		- Many Kotlin objects have adapter methods that usually start with "to" as a prefix.
			ex) "toTypedArray()": converts a list to an array.

	- Adapter pattern helps bridge different concepts and implementations.